        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on the ease with which different species of <hi rend="italic">Felis</hi> can be tamed.</p> 
            <p>Asian species of wild cattle.</p>
            <p>Variation in colour of jackals.</p> 
<p>Discusses the difficulties of differentiating between varieties and species. EB recommends Herman Schlegel’s definition of species [in <hi rend="italic">Essay on the physiognomy of serpents</hi>, trans. T. S. Traill (1843)]. Problems of defining species of wolves and squirrels. Pigeons and doves afford an illustration of "clusters of <hi rend="italic">species</hi>, <hi rend="italic">varieties</hi>, or races". Various pigeons have local species in different parts of India and Burma, some of which interbreed where their ranges cross; as do the local species of <hi rend="italic">Coracias</hi> [see <hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>, p. 259].</p> 
            <p>[CD’s notes are an abstract of this memorandum.]</p>
        </abstract>
